  "occupation": "Board Director at Outdoor Media Association",
  "headline": "Executive Leader | Business Development & Commercial Strategy | Brand & Market Positioning",
  "summary": "With more than 27 years’ experience across media and Out of Home advertising, I have built a career at the intersection of commercial strategy, infrastructure delivery and long term partnership development.\n\nMy experience spans retail media, transit, airports, large format, street furniture and digital Out of Home, with deep expertise in concession based environments, public transport networks and government and commercial partnerships. I have led the development and growth of national portfolios, overseen complex tender submissions, negotiated long term contracts and revenue share models, and guided businesses through periods of significant transformation and innovation.\n\nI am particularly experienced in translating complex environments into commercially viable, high performing media solutions. This includes portfolio strategy, revenue modelling, digitisation, operational execution, stakeholder management and building high performing teams that deliver consistently for partners and clients.\n\nOut of Home remains one of the most resilient and powerful media channels. It continues to evolve through digitisation, data and new environments, while retaining its core strength as an always on, unavoidable medium that delivers scale, impact and efficiency. I am deeply passionate about ensuring Out of Home remains central to media schedules and continues to offer advertisers flexible, accountable and effective solutions.\n\nI thrive on collaboration, innovation and creating partnerships that deliver mutual value. I am excited by what lies ahead and the opportunity to apply my experience, insight and leadership to the next chapter.",
  "location_str": "Cremorne, New South Wales, Australia",
